<module>
  <title>dèan</title>
  <p><strong>dèan</strong> is an irregular <a href="?xx=verbs/verbs">verb</a>, with the basic meaning <en>do, make</en>.</p>
  <hr/>
  <h5><m>dèan</m> in lexicalised verb expressions</h5>
  <p><strong>dèan</strong> + <a href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjective</a> –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>sleamhainn</i> <en>slippery</en> ⇒ <m>dèan sleamhainn</m> <en>lubricate</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>dèan</strong> + <a href="?xx=nouns/common_nouns">common noun</a> denoting an activity –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>cùl-mhùtaireachd</i> <en>smuggle</en> ⇒ <m>dèan cùl-mhùtaireachd</m> <en>smuggle</en></li>
    <li><i>eadar-ghuidh</i> <en>intercede</en> ⇒ <i>eadar-ghuidhe</i> <en>intercession</en> ⇒ <m>dèan eadar-ghuidhe</m> <en>intercede</en></li>
    <li><i>geur-lean</i> <en>persecute</en> ⇒ <i>geur-leanmhainn</i> <en>persecution</en> ⇒ <m>dèan geur-leanmhainn (air)</m> <en>persecute</en></li>
  </ul>
</module>
